  "prompt": "How widely accepted are credit cards at small businesses and restaurants in Malta?",
  "response": "In Malta, credit card acceptance is quite widespread, even among small businesses and restaurants, though there are some nuances to be aware of:\n\n### **1. Urban Areas and Tourist Hotspots**\nIn cities like Valletta, Sliema, St. Julian's, and Mdina, as well as in popular tourist areas, credit cards (especially Visa and Mastercard) are widely accepted. Most restaurants, cafes, and shops in these areas will have card payment facilities.\n\n### **2. Small Businesses and Rural Areas**\nIn smaller towns or rural areas, some small businesses, local eateries, or family-run establishments might only accept cash or have a minimum spending requirement for card payments. This is more common in less touristy locations.\n\n### **3. Debit vs. Credit Cards**\nDebit cards are universally accepted wherever card payments are available, and they are the preferred payment method for many locals. Credit cards are also accepted but may incur additional fees in some cases.\n\n### **4. Mobile Payments and Contactless**\nContactless payments (via cards or mobile wallets like Apple Pay and Google Pay) are increasingly common, especially in larger businesses and restaurants.\n\n### **5. Tips for Travelers**\n- Always carry some cash, especially if you plan to visit smaller establishments or rural areas.\n- Check for card payment signs or ask beforehand if you\u2019re unsure.\n- Be aware that smaller businesses might prefer cash for smaller transactions to avoid card processing fees.\n\nOverall, while credit card acceptance is quite high in Malta, it\u2019s prudent to have a mix of payment options to ensure convenience during your visit.",
